text:
My mom called during class today.

She thought it was my lunch break.

I answered. We talked briefly. I told her I loved her.

Then, I told my kids, "When Mom calls, you gotta answer."

We laughed. We got back to work. 

Phones aren't ruining education. Ed's got bigger problems.
